content_html: Chitwan, Sept 15: Five persons died from Japanese encephalitis in Chitwan district so far in the current fiscal year. Out of 16 infected persons, five lost lives. Chief of District Health Office, Chitwan, Dinesh Rupakheti said a 42-year-old woman of Rapti municipality died from Japanese encephalitis on September 23.
